  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a single color override for a font palette entry.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontPaletteOverride` pairs a palette entry index with a replacement color. Pass a
span of overrides to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.PaletteOverrides> to substitute
individual colors in a font's CPAL palette at typeface-clone time.

The `Color` field is a raw `sk_color_t` value (ARGB, `0xAARRGGBB`) equivalent to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var overrides = new[]
{
    new SKFontPaletteOverride { Index = 0, Color = (uint)SKColors.CornflowerBlue },
};
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    PaletteIndex = 0,
    PaletteOverrides = overrides,
};
using var clone = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
